<p>I'm using Hangfire in my MVC webapp. I configured it this way:</p>  <pre><code>GlobalConfiguration.Configuration          .UseMongoStorage(mongoConnectionString, mongoDatabaseName);  app.UseHangfireServer(); </code></pre>  <p>When I run the application I see <code>IIS Worker Process</code> takes constantly almost 40% CPU.  </p>  <p>Removing it brings the application to works normally.</p>  <p>What's wrong?  </p>